%[text] ### Unoptimized Portfolio Comparison
%[text] To determine the risk and expected return, we examined the historical drawdown, 5-factor exposure, and efficiency of each portfolio.
plotForecastedReturns(portfolios); %[output:3cc22eff]
plotHistoricalDrawdown(portfolios, colors(1:length(portfolios), :)); %[output:42f09fee]
plotFactorExposures(portfolios); %[output:7c15d945]
plotEfficientFrontier(portfolios, colors(1:length(portfolios), :)); %[output:1a3becc5] %[output:07e9c384] %[output:280e9362]
%[text] The various 5-factor models based on AVGE all cluster close to the efficient frontier. The US + International portfolio does well in terms of efficiency, however it has a more conservative risk profile. This is likely due to the gold exposure. It may make sense to consider including gold exposure in the optimization process to see how it can help hedge risk. Despite this, given that I am young, it makes sense to pursue a more risk-tolerant portfolio. My current portfolio far exceeds all proposed portfolios in terms of risk, however it has similair expected annual returns to the 5-factor based portfolios. VT significantly underperforms the AVGE based portfolios both in risk and return.
%[text] Based on these results, it make sense to further explore 5-factor based models, specifically optimizing the growth weighting. Additionally, gold will be considered for its drastic reduction in risk. VT will not be considered going forward as a sole holding due to its pore performance relative to all other proposed portfolios. My current portfolio will be optimized as a reference point. 
